HEADWORD: Crumbcloth
<hw>Crumb"cloth`</hw> <pr>(-kl⟦ocr⟧th`; 115)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
cloth to be laid under a dining table to receive falling fragments, and
keep the carpet or floor clean.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>crumcloth</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

